  &lt;p id="pMuYN0"&gt;Casio Japan is releasing a new desk clock that will be familiar to those who’ve eschewed smartwatches in favor of simpler digital timepieces. It’s a &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.casio.com%2Fjp%2Fwatches%2Fcasio%2Fclock%2Fproduct.DQD-851J-8%2F&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F10%2F9%2F24265964%2Fcasio-digital-watch-desk-a158w-clock-japan-retro-vintage" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;supersized version&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.casio.com%2Fca-en%2Fwatches%2Fcasio%2Fproduct.A158WA-1%2F&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F10%2F9%2F24265964%2Fcasio-digital-watch-desk-a158w-clock-japan-retro-vintage" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Casio A158W&lt;/a&gt; digital watch that could make for a great nightstand alarm clock, although you may not want to hide its retro charm in your bedroom.&lt;/p&gt;
