&lt;p id="TXHODr"&gt;DeepMind CEO Demis Hassabis and senior DeepMind research scientist John Jumper received the award for creating the open-source AlphaFold2 AI model to calculate the structure of human proteins. “With its help, they have been able to predict the structure of virtually all the 200 million proteins that researchers have identified,” the Nobel committee at the Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences &lt;a href="https://www.nobelprize.org/prizes/chemistry/2024/press-release/"&gt;said in its announcement&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
