  &lt;p id="d59KYx"&gt;Ring’s new &lt;a href="https://blog.ring.com/"&gt;Smart Video Search&lt;/a&gt; lets you search through recorded footage to find everything from a lost cat to a red sweater. According to Ring, the AI-powered feature can locate specific events in your Ring video history based on natural language searches, such as “a black cat at night,” “a red truck in the rain,” and “a kid riding a bike yesterday.” Compared to Ring’s current smart notifications, which can alert you to doorbell rings, people, or packages, Smart Video Search opens up a whole new level of historical insight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="xkPOnn"&gt;The feature is launching today in beta for users in the US with the &lt;a href="https://ring.com/protect-pro"&gt;Ring Protect Pro plan&lt;/a&gt; ($19.99 a month). At launch, &lt;a href="https://blog.ring.com/"&gt;Ring says&lt;/a&gt; it can search for queries related to animals, vehicles, packages, and people, which can...&lt;/p&gt;
